      <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersS95"/>
      <p><a href="ch71s13.html#MonstersS95">Sphinxes</a> are enigmatic creatures with great, feathery wings and leonine bodies. All <a href="ch71s13.html#MonstersS95">sphinxes</a> are territorial, but the more intelligent ones can differentiate between deliberate intrusion and temporary or inadvertent trespass.</p>
      <p>A typical <a href="ch71s13.html#MonstersS95">sphinx</a> is about 10 feet long and weighs about 800 pounds.</p>
      <p><a href="ch71s13.html#MonstersS95">Sphinxes</a> speak <a href="ch71s13.html#MonstersS95">Sphinx</a>, Common, and Draconic.</p>
      <div class="sect4" lang="en">
        <div class="titlepage">
          <div>
            <div>
              <h5 class="title"><a name="id2185349"/>Combat</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
          <div class="keyword">monsterinfo</div>
        </div>
        <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersS96"/>
        <p>Most <a href="ch71s13.html#MonstersS95">sphinxes</a> fight on the ground, using their wings to help them pounce much as <a href="ch73s24.html#MonstersAnimals84">lions</a> do. If outnumbered by earthbound creatures, a <a href="ch71s13.html#MonstersS95">sphinx</a> takes wing and attacks on the fly.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2185469"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersS97"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Pounce (Ex):</strong></span> If a <a href="ch71s13.html#MonstersS95">sphinx</a> charges a foe, it can make a full attack, including two rake attacks.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2185508"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersS98"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Rake (Ex):</strong></span> A <a href="ch71s13.html#MonstersS95">sphinx</a> that pounces onto a creature can make two rake attacks with its hind legs. Each <a href="ch71s13.html#MonstersS95">sphinx's</a> description provides its attack bonus and damage.</p>
          <p/>
        </div>
